  "text": "Finally, the changes in inflammatory markers in response to tesamorelin were of relatively small magnitude, and, as the study did not measure clinical cardiovascular endpoints, these changes are of uncertain clinical significance. Moreover, metformin appears to have a larger effect on PAI-1 in this population and may have a more significant effect on tPA [CITATION_1] . Although tesamorelin should not be used for the primary purpose of improving these markers, modest effects to decrease tPA antigen and increase adiponectin may be relevant associated benefits of its use to reduce VAT.",
